
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "WorkItem";
}
<main role="main-inner-wrapper" class="container">
    <div class="work-details">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-4">
                <header role="work-title">
                    <h2>Chrome Extension Admin/Online MO Wallet</h2>
                    <a href="#">Project URL: Private <i class="fa fa-lock" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
                </header>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-8">
                <section>
                    <p>This is an MVC admin site made to support my <a href="../Work/Project?project=ChromeExtension">Chrome extension</a>. It is still unfinished as priority is now my token presale site. This serves as a taster of what is to come (displayed on presale site).</p>
                    <p>The user is able to manage everything from the extension such as activity, transactions, user details and statistics of usage on the network. I plan to extend the current WebAPI (for the extension) backend to allow for serving statistics from direct calls.</p>
                    <p>Current implementation requires <a href="https://metamask.io/">Metamask</a> to be installed to interact with blockchain as i use the injected Web3 Javascript object - this is going to change.</p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Details</strong><br />
                        MVC Razor C#
                        .NET Framework 4.5.2 &
                        Microsoft SQL Server
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="clearfix"></div>
        <div class="work-images grid">
            <ul class="grid-lod effect-2" id="grid">
                <li>
                    <p class="left-align">This is the login page where users sign in.</p>
                    <a href="~/images/work-images/mo-login.png" class="pointer">
                        <img src="~/images/work-images/mo-login.png" alt="" class="img-responsive" />
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
